'''Gokana kingdom''' is one of the six kingdoms of the [[Ogoni people]] in [[Ogoni]] (also Ogoniland) in the [[Niger Delta]] region of [[Nigeria]]. "Gokana kingdom" has geographic, historic and ethno-linguistic elements with some 130,000 [[Gokana language]] speakers located in the [[Gokana, Nigeria| Gokana Local Government Area]] in [[Rivers State]]. Gokana contains a number of villages, including Lewe, B. Dere, K. Dere, Kpor, Mogho, Bomu, Bodo, Gio-koo, Nwe-ol, Alli D. Bera, Biara, Deeyor, Boghor, Barako and Yeghe.<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://jas.sagepub.com/cgi/content/abstract/41/1-2/13 |title=Birth of the Ogoni Protest Movement | last =Osha | first =Sanya | journal = Journal of Asian and African Studies | volume =41 | issue =1-2 | pages =13–38 |year = 2006 |DOI= 10.1177/0021909606061746
|accessdate=2010-06-26 |quote= |work= }}</ref><ref>Earlier version of same article.{{cite web|url=http://www.ukzn.ac.za/ccs/files/CCS_RREPORTS2_REPORT33.pdf |title=Birth of the Ogoni Protest Movement |last=Osha |first=Sanya |year=2005 |accessdate=2010-06-26 |quote= |publisher=Centre for Civil Society, [[University of KwaZulu-Natal]] |format=pdf }}{{dead link|date=January 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

