{{EngvarB|date=July 2013}} {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Tom Hopper | image = | caption = | fullname = Thomas Edward Hopper<ref>{{cite web |title=EFL: Club list of registered players |url=https://www.efl.com/siteassets/efl-documents/efl-released-and-retained-list---2016-17.pdf |publisher=English Football League |format=PDF |page=62 |date=20 May 2017 |accessdate=6 October 2017}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1993|12|14|df=y}}<ref name="11v11">{{cite web |url=https://www.11v11.com/players/tom-hopper-237420/ |title=Tom Hopper|website=11v11.com |publisher=AFS Enterprises |accessdate=21 July 2018}}</ref> | birth_place = [[Boston, Lincolnshire|Boston]], England<ref>{{cite book|editor1-first=Glenda|editor1-last=Rollin|editor2-first=Jack|editor2-last=Rollin|title=Sky Sports Football Yearbook 2012–2013|year=2012|publisher=[[Headline Publishing Group|Headline]]|location=London|isbn=978-0-7553-6356-8|page=484|edition=43rd}}</ref> | death_date = <!--{{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD||||df=y}}--> | height = {{convert|1.86|m|order=flip}}<ref name="11v11"/> | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | currentclub = [[Southend United F.C.|Southend United]] | clubnumber = 9 | youthyears1 = 2006–2010| youthclubs1 = [[Boston United F.C.|Boston United]] | youthyears2 = 2010–2011| youthclubs2 = [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] | years1 = 2011–2015| clubs1 = [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]]| caps1 = 0| goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2012–2013| clubs2 = → [[Bury F.C.|Bury]] (loan) | caps2 = 22| goals2 = 3 | years3 = 2015 | clubs3 = → [[Scunthorpe United F.C.|Scunthorpe United]] (loan) | caps3 = 12| goals3 = 4 | years4 = 2015–2018| clubs4 = [[Scunthorpe United F.C.|Scunthorpe United]] | caps4 = 91| goals4 = 18 | years5 = 2018–| clubs5 = [[Southend United F.C.|Southend United]] | caps5 = 12| goals5 = 6 | club-update = 10:14, 11 October 2018 (UTC) }} '''Thomas Edward Hopper''' (born 14 December 1993) is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Southend United F.C.|Southend United]].
==Club career==
===Early career=== Tom Hopper began his career with [[Boston United]]. Hopper became Boston's youngest ever player, when aged 15 he came on as a substitute for goalscorer [[Spencer Weir-Daley]] for the final 13 minutes of a 2–1 Challenge Cup victory over [[Hucknall Town]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Hopper makes Boston United history|url=http://www.bostonstandard.co.uk/sport/hopper-makes-boston-united-history-1-1116572|publisher=The Boston Standard|date=25 November 2009|accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref> In the summer of 2010, Hopper signed for [[Leicester City]] and immediately began impressing in the club's youth teams.
===Leicester City=== Hopper signed his first professional contract with [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] in October 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lcfc.com/page/LatestNews/0,,10274~2475259,00.html |title=Tom Hopper Signs Pro Contract |publisher=Leicester City F.C. |accessdate=1 March 2015 |date=7 October 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111009074328/http://www.lcfc.com/page/LatestNews/0,,10274~2475259,00.html |archivedate=9 October 2011 |deadurl=unfit }}</ref> On 28 January 2012, Hopper was allocated the number 37 shirt and named on the substitutes bench for Leicester's [[FA Cup]] match against [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]]. He made his début as an 81st-minute substitute for [[David Nugent]]. Leicester won the match 2–0.<ref>{{cite news|title=Jermaine Beckford continued his superb scoring record in the FA Cup with both goals against a plucky Swindon side|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/16664158|accessdate=22 August 2012|newspaper=[[BBC Sport]]|date=28 January 2012}}</ref> Hopper said of his debut that "It all seems like a blur, but something I have really enjoyed".<ref>{{cite news|title=Leicester City academy striker Hopper straight back to earth – cleaning boots!|url=http://www.thisisleicestershire.co.uk/story-15087221-detail/story.html|accessdate=22 August 2012|newspaper=Leicester Mercury|date=31 January 2012}}</ref>
Manager [[Nigel Pearson]] was said to be impressed by the youngster.<ref>{{cite news|title=Academy prospect Tom Hopper making big impression with Leicester City|url=http://www.thisisleicestershire.co.uk/Academy-prospect-Tom-Hopper-making-big-impression/story-15332609-detail/story.html|accessdate=22 August 2012|newspaper=Leicester Mercury|date=27 February 2012}}</ref> In May 2012, he was named as Leicester City's Academy Player of the Season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Tom Hopper's season to savour with Leicester City ends with top Foxes award|url=http://www.bostonstandard.co.uk/sport/football/tom-hopper-s-season-to-savour-with-leicester-city-ends-with-top-foxes-award-1-3818670|accessdate=22 August 2012|newspaper=Boston Standard|date=12 May 2012}}</ref> Hopper was given the 21 number for the 2012–13 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lcfc.com/news/article/030812-first-team-squad-numbers-confirmed-293774.aspx |title=Leicester City First Team Squad Numbers Confirmed |publisher=Leicester City F.C. |accessdate=1 March 2015 |date=3 August 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140813210333/http://www.lcfc.com/news/article/030812-first-team-squad-numbers-confirmed-293774.aspx |archivedate=13 August 2014 |deadurl=unfit }}</ref> On 14 September, Hopper joined [[Bury F.C.|Bury]] on a one-month loan deal.<ref name="Bury loan for Hopper">{{cite web|title=Bury loan for Hopper |url=http://www.lcfc.com/news/article/140912-bury-loan-for-hopper-366711.aspx |publisher=Leicester City F.C. |work=www.LCFC.com |date=14 September 2012 |accessdate=14 September 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120917054730/http://www.lcfc.com/news/article/140912-bury-loan-for-hopper-366711.aspx |archivedate=17 September 2012 |deadurl=unfit }}</ref> Hopper scored twice in his first six games during a month-long loan spell at Bury, including his first ever professional league goal against [[Stevenage F.C.|Stevenage]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Stevenage 2-2 Bury|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/19684295|publisher=BBC Sport|date=27 September 2012|accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref> and [[Crawley Town F.C.|Crawley Town]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Crawley Town 3-2 Bury|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/19854924|publisher=BBC Sport|date=12 October 2012|accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref> On 16 October Hopper extended his loan at Bury until 3 January 2013, which was then extended for the remaineder of the 2012–13 season on 4 January 2013.<ref name="Young pros extend loan spells">{{cite web|url=http://www.lcfc.com/news/article/040113-young-pros-extend-loan-spells-578398.aspx |title=Young Pro extend loan spells |publisher=Leicester City F.C. |work=www.LCFC.co.uk |date=4 January 2013 |accessdate=4 January 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140531105444/http://www.lcfc.com/news/article/040113-young-pros-extend-loan-spells-578398.aspx |archivedate=31 May 2014 |deadurl=unfit }}</ref> Hopper's loan spell was cut short and he was sent back to Leicester on 7 February 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.buryfc.co.uk/news/article/hopper-returns-to-leicester-643601.aspx |title=Hopper returns to Leicester |publisher=Bury F.C. |accessdate=1 March 2015 |date=7 February 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130211145658/http://www.buryfc.co.uk/news/article/hopper-returns-to-leicester-643601.aspx |archivedate=11 February 2013 |deadurl=unfit }}</ref>
Hopper finished the season with [[Leicester City Development Squad & Academy]], helping them to win the 2012–13 Professional Development League 2 and the [[HKFC International Soccer Sevens]] cup tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lcfc.com/news/article/080313-under-21s-seal-top-spot-with-3-0-win-760282.aspx |title=U21s Seal Top Spot With 3–0 Win |publisher=lcfc.com |accessdate=1 March 2015 |date=8 April 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130527002101/http://www.lcfc.com/news/article/080313-under-21s-seal-top-spot-with-3-0-win-760282.aspx |archivedate=27 May 2013 |deadurl=unfit }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lcfc.com/news/article/260513-foxes-secure-hong-kong-sevens-crown-835455.aspx |title=Foxes Secure Hong Kong Sevens Crown |publisher=lcfc.com |accessdate=1 March 2015 |date=26 May 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130616235730/http://www.lcfc.com/news/article/260513-foxes-secure-hong-kong-sevens-crown-835455.aspx |archivedate=16 June 2013 |deadurl=unfit }}</ref> Hopper was allocated the number 20 shirt at the beginning of the 2013–14 season<ref>{{cite news|title=Leicester City announce squad numbers for 2013-14 season|url=http://www.leicestermercury.co.uk/Leicester-City-announce-squad-numbers-2013-14/story-19568833-detail/story.html|publisher=Leicester Mercury|date=25 July 2013|accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref> and was named as an unused substitute in Leicester's 2–1 [[2013–14 Football League Cup|Football League Cup]] win over [[Wycombe Wanderers F.C.|Wycombe Wanderers]] on 6 August. He made his first appearance of the season in the next round of the League Cup, replacing Chris Wood in the 66th minute of a 5–2 win at [[Carlisle United F.C.|Carlisle United]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/23764121|title=Carlisle 2–5 Leicester|publisher=BBC Sport|date=27 August 2013}}</ref> On 30 May 2014, Hopper signed a new two-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lcfc.com/news/article/300514-new-deal-for-hopper-1591157.aspx |title=New Deal for Hopper |publisher=Leicester City FC |date=30 May 2014 |accessdate=31 May 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140530195413/http://www.lcfc.com/news/article/300514-new-deal-for-hopper-1591157.aspx |archivedate=30 May 2014 |deadurl=unfit }}</ref>
Hopper was an unused substitute in Leicester's first two [[Premier League]] fixtures, against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] and [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] in August 2014.
===Scunthorpe United=== On 8 January 2015, Hopper joined [[Football League One|League One]] outfit [[Scunthorpe United F.C.|Scunthorpe United]] on a one-month loan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lcfc.com/news/article/hopper-heads-to-scunthorpe-on-loan-2189242.aspx |title=Hopper Heads To Scunthorpe On Loan |publisher=Leicester City |date=8 January 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150109011921/http://www.lcfc.com/news/article/hopper-heads-to-scunthorpe-on-loan-2189242.aspx |archivedate=9 January 2015 |deadurl=unfit }}</ref> Hopper made his debut on 10 January 2015, scoring in the 4–1 victory against [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scunthorpe-united.co.uk/news/article/report-walsall-1-4-iron-2194299.aspx |title=REPORT: WALSALL 1–4 IRON |publisher=Scunthorpe United |date=10 January 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150110191902/http://www.scunthorpe-united.co.uk/news/article/report-walsall-1-4-iron-2194299.aspx |archivedate=10 January 2015 |deadurl=unfit }}</ref> After scoring 4 goals in 4 games, Hopper's loan was extended until the end on the season on 2 February 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lcfc.com/news/article/hopper-extends-scunthorpe-loan-2243164.aspx |title=Hopper Extends Scunthorpe Loan |publisher=Leicester City |date=2 February 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150202184606/http://www.lcfc.com/news/article/hopper-extends-scunthorpe-loan-2243164.aspx |archivedate=2 February 2015 |deadurl=unfit }}</ref> Hopper was nominated for the Sky Bet League One Player of the Month award for January, missing out to [[Dele Alli]] of [[MK Dons]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-league.co.uk/news/article/2015/sky-bet-league-1-player-of-the-month-nominations-2246162.aspx |title=Sky Bet League 1 Player of the Month nominations |publisher=Football League |date=4 February 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150207124340/http://www.football-league.co.uk/news/article/2015/sky-bet-league-1-player-of-the-month-nominations-2246162.aspx |archivedate=7 February 2015 |deadurl=unfit }}</ref> After his Leicester contract was terminated, he joined Scunthorpe on a permanent basis on 26 June 2015.<ref>{{cite news|title=Tom Hopper: Scunthorpe sign sacked Leicester City striker|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/33288153|accessdate=26 June 2015|work=BBC Sport|date=26 June 2015}}</ref>
===Southend United===
Hopper signed for [[Southend United F.C.|Southend United]] on 15 June 2018 on a three year deal.<ref>https://www.southendunited.co.uk/news/2018/june/hopper-is-a-blue/</ref> He scored on his debut in a 3-2 defeat to [[Doncaster Rovers F.C.|Doncaster Rovers]].<ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44989249</ref>
==Personal life==
In May 2015, Hopper and teammates [[James Pearson (footballer, born 1993)|James Pearson]] and [[Adam Smith (footballer, born 1992)|Adam Smith]] made a [[Amateur pornography|sex tape]] with local women on Leicester's tour of Thailand, which was obtained by the ''[[Sunday Mirror]]''. The three players apologised for making the video, which included a racial epithet towards the women.<ref>{{cite news|title=Leicester City trio apologise for behaviour on Thailand tour|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-leicestershire-32950519|accessdate=31 May 2015|work=BBC News|date=31 May 2015}}</ref> Following the outcome of disciplinary proceedings, the three players had their contracts terminated.
